data.name: h_desc
data.value: Either shows a help for a single command, or DMs you help link if no arguments are specified.

data.name: donate_desc
data.value: Instructions for helping the project financially.

data.name: commands_desc
data.value: List all of the bot's commands from a certain module. You can either specify full, or only first few letters of the module name.

data.name: greetdel_desc
data.value: Toggles automatic deletion of greet messages.

data.name: greet_desc
data.value: Toggles anouncements on the current channel when someone joins the server.

data.name: greetmsg_desc
data.value: Sets a new join announcement message which will be shown in the server's channel. Type %user% if you want to mention the new member. Using it with no message will show the current greet message.

data.name: bye_desc
data.value: Toggles anouncements on the current channel when someone leaves the server.

data.name: byemsg_desc
data.value: Sets a new leave announcement message. Type %user% if you want to mention the new member. Using it with no message will show the current bye message.

data.name: byedel_desc
data.value: Toggles automatic deletion of bye messages.

data.name: greetdm_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the greet messages will be sent in a DM (This is separate from greet - you can have both, any or neither enabled).

data.name: spmom_desc
data.value: Toggles whether mentions of other offline users on your server will send a pm to them.

data.name: logserver_desc
data.value: Logs server activity in this channel.

data.name: logignore_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the .logserver command ignores this channel. Useful if you have hidden admin channel and public log channel.

data.name: userpresence_desc
data.value: Starts logging to this channel when someone from the server goes online/offline/idle.

data.name: voicepresence_desc
data.value: Toggles logging to this channel whenever someone joins or leaves a voice channel you are in right now.

data.name: repeatinvoke_desc
data.value: Immediately shows the repeat message and restarts the timer.

data.name: repeat_desc
data.value: Repeat a message every X minutes. If no parameters are specified, repeat is disabled.

data.name: rotateplaying_desc
data.value: Toggles rotation of playing status of the dynamic strings you specified earlier.

data.name: addplaying_desc
data.value: Adds a specified string to the list of playing strings to rotate. Supported placeholders: %servers%, %users%, %playing%, %queued%

data.name: listplaying_desc
data.value: Lists all playing statuses with their corresponding number.

data.name: removeplaying_desc
data.value: Removes a playing string on a given number.

data.name: slowmode_desc
data.value: Toggles slow mode. When ON, users will be able to send only 1 message every 5 seconds.

data.name: cleanvplust_desc
data.value: Deletes all text channels ending in `-voice` for which voicechannels are not found. **Use at your own risk. Needs Manage Roles and Manage Channels Permissions.**

data.name: voiceplustext_desc
data.value: Creates a text channel for each voice channel only users in that voice channel can see.If you are server owner, keep in mind you will see them all the time regardless.

data.name: scsc_desc
data.value: Starts an instance of cross server channel. You will get a token as a DM that other people will use to tune in to the same instance.

data.name: jcsc_desc
data.value: Joins current channel to an instance of cross server channel using the token.

data.name: lcsc_desc
data.value: Leaves Cross server channel instance from this channel.

data.name: asar_desc
data.value: Adds a role, or list of roles separated by whitespace(use quotations for multiword roles) to the list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: rsar_desc
data.value: Removes a specified role from the list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: tesar_desc
data.value: Toggles whether the self-assigned roles are exclusive. (So that any person can have only one of the self assignable roles)

data.name: iam_desc
data.value: Adds a role to you that you choose. Role must be on a list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: iamnot_desc
data.value: Removes a role to you that you choose. Role must be on a list of self-assignable roles.

data.name: addcustreact_desc
data.value: Add a custom reaction with a trigger and a response. Running this command in server requires Administration permission. Running this command in DM is Bot Owner only and adds a new global custom reaction. Guide here: <http://nadekobot.readthedocs.io/en/1.0/Custom%20Reactions/>

data.name: listcustreact_desc
data.value: Lists global or server custom reactions (15 commands per page). Running the command in DM will list global custom reactions, while running it in server will list that server's custom reactions.

data.name: showcustreact_desc
data.value: Shows a custom reaction's response on a given ID.

data.name: editcustreact_desc
data.value: Edits a custom reaction, arguments are custom reactions name, index to change, and a (multiword) message.

data.name: delcustreact_desc
data.value: Deletes a custom reaction on a specific index. If ran in DM, it is bot owner only and deletes a global custom reaction. If ran in a server, it requires Administration priviledges and removes server custom reaction.

data.name: autoassignrole_desc
data.value: Automaticaly assigns a specified role to every user who joins the server.

data.name: autoassignrole_usage
data.value: `.aar` to disable, `.aar Role Name` to enable

data.name: leave_desc
data.value: Makes Nadeko leave the server. Either name or id required.

data.name: listincidents_desc
data.value: List all UNREAD incidents and flags them as read.

data.name: listallincidents_desc
data.value: Sends you a file containing all incidents and flags them as read.

data.name: delmsgoncmd_desc
data.value: Toggles the automatic deletion of user's successful command message to prevent chat flood. **Server Manager Only.**

data.name: restart_desc
data.value: Restarts the bot. Might not work.

data.name: setrole_desc
data.value: Sets a role for a given user.

data.name: removerole_desc
data.value: Removes a role from a given user.

data.name: renamerole_desc
data.value: Renames a role. Roles you are renaming must be lower than bot's highest role.

data.name: removeallroles_desc
data.value: Removes all roles from a mentioned user.

data.name: createrole_desc
data.value: Creates a role with a given name.

data.name: rolecolor_desc
data.value: Set a role's color to the hex or 0-255 rgb color value provided.

data.name: ban_desc
data.value: Bans a user by id or name with an optional message.

data.name: softban_desc
data.value: Bans and then unbans a user by id or name with an optional message.

data.name: mute_desc
data.value: Mutes a mentioned user in a voice channel.

data.name: delvoichanl_desc
data.value: Deletes a voice channel with a given name.

data.name: creatvoichanl_desc
data.value: Creates a new voice channel with a given name.

data.name: deltxtchanl_desc
data.value: Deletes a text channel with a given name.

data.name: creatxtchanl_desc
data.value: Creates a new text channel with a given name.

data.name: settopic_desc
data.value: Sets a topic on the current channel.

data.name: setchanlname_desc
data.value: Changed the name of the current channel.

data.value: `.prune` removes all nadeko's messages in the last 100 messages.`.prune X` removes last X messages from the channel (up to 100)`.prune @Someone` removes all Someone's messages in the last 100 messages.`.prune @Someone X` removes last X 'Someone's' messages in the channel.

data.name: die_desc
data.value: Works only for the owner. Shuts the bot down.

data.name: setname_desc
data.value: Give the bot a new name.

data.name: setavatar_desc
data.value: Sets a new avatar image for the NadekoBot. Argument is a direct link to an image.

data.name: send_desc
data.value: Sends a message to someone on a different server through the bot. Separate server and channel/user ids with `|` and prepend channel id with `c:` and user id with `u:`.

data.value: Mentions every person from the provided role or roles (separated by a ',') on this server. Requires you to have mention everyone permission.

data.name: donators_desc
data.value: List of lovely people who donated to keep this project alive.

data.name: donadd_desc
data.value: Add a donator to the database.

data.name: savechat_desc
data.value: Saves a number of messages to a text file and sends it to you.

data.value: Sends a message to you or a channel after certain amount of time. First argument is me/here/'channelname'. Second argument is time in a descending order (mo>w>d>h>m) example: 1w5d3h10m. Third argument is a (multiword)message.

data.value: `.remind me 1d5h Do something` or `.remind #general Start now!`

data.value: Sets message for when the remind is triggered. Available placeholders are %user% - user who ran the command, %message% - Message specified in the remind, %target% - target channel of the remind.

data.name: whosplaying_desc

data.name: dysyd_desc
